It is clearly a crime that the Greatest Model Of All Time seems not to be available in a teeny form so hopefully this goes some way to fixing that.

This is a reworking of Miffles (now sadly) 'missing' (ğŸ™„) dreadnought; I've included those files in the 'miffles original' folder. I started this years ago and only dug it out again recently. Alas, my CAD skills are very much in the noob-zone (hence the name of the model) so apologies for both the woeful nature of some of the hack-n-slashing and also the resulting files sizes. I'm revving up a campaign of nagging any of those Legends of our hobby (Woddish, Jimmyzimms, KMFP, Daffmakes, Mildseven etc) to actually do it properly. Fingers crossed :).

This is the Grim version, over which I have plastered a load of bolts and various other gubbins. I've included a load of body versions, with different torso angles and feet orientations: I'm sure you'll work it all out from the file names. I've also included looser-fitting mount options in case your resin tolerance can't take the snugger version. The identifier 'small' for the legs is in juxtaposition to a 'large' version I trialled (about 110% enbiggening of legs). I like the Deadpool-2-re-growing look of the originals but if any of you want something that looks a bit less top-heavy then let me know and I might finish the re-work.

I've done 'TrueScale' (top of head, not to eye) 8mm versions and also 10mm for easier re-scaling (so, for example, if you game in 18mm just print at 180%).

I may also do another upload with some non-bolty Tech monopose versions, with the larger legs, for a more hard-scif vibe.

Cheers

Kipples

PS: The '0-mount' identifier in the file names means I haven't put any mount rings on the body. I've tried this for the Tech version, though, which has a single ring spacer for the mounts so they're less flush with the torso.

These are remixes from Vohvel's excellent originals:

https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4862377

I've used some other bits and bobs also, such as JayMull420's glyphs and Alpokemon's quite frankly wonderful chibi tiger:

https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4694469

https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2391204

Update:
See also Cwen's excellent mods of the above base designs over on his Cults page. Nice!
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/y-orc-battle-lorries-8mm-scale/comments#comment-answer-734601

I did these a couple of years ago so I may have forgotten someone's bits: please let me know if so. I'm a bit of a noob with MeshMixer so, again, apologies if for anything messy. I've basically embedded guns in the front, added peg-turrets and given lots of glyph/no glyph [clean] options. They've all printed fine my end so fingers crossed yours. If you have problems with the pegs not fitting the holes properly then just resize the turrets a bit as some resins cure with odd dimensions. These are re-sized to what I think orks should roughly be on the Moonjammy scale (so 90% of Vohvel's originals)? Hope you enjoy using them to munch humies. Waaagh!

UPDATE: 2023-10-11
I didn't expect quite so many downloads so to I've done some extra bits last night that I was going to leave till Christmas. Essentially just some fiddling to create more variety (orks don't really do 'standardised', do they :) ). More glyph options (the numbers correlate with those in JayMull420's pack for those wanting to fiddle more), some new turrets and, crucially, bolted versions of the dozer glyphs in addition to the welded. Hope you enjoy them and any donations to the originators listed above, please, rather than me. Cheers.

I got frustrated with the lack of decent blast markers out there so I asked TimsTanks if he would kindly let me remix his:

https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4532903

I'm pretty much a MeshMixer noob so apologies for the mess. I did some fixed versions in MeshMixer and various other programs but was worried they might muck up as they print fine as they are in my experience (as you can see from the photos). If anyone with more skill wants to fix them/make them solid for greater utility feel free. I did a load of versions and obviously you can mirror them for even more variety. If you want to donate, please do it to TimsTanks. Ta.
